<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB08425</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT ESTABLISHING AN INTERNAL AFFAIRS SERVICE IN THE BUREAU OF IMMIGRATION AND APPROPRIATING FUNDS THEREFOR</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Seeks to maintain, promote, and ensure the Bureau of Immigration's high standard of ethics in
public service through the establishment of an Internal Affairs Service.

It shall serve as a monitoring, investigatory, recommendatory and disciplinary body whose primary objective is to ensure that the Bureau is instilling and strengthening responsibility and accountability among its personnel. 

